title: Labour MP Tom Watson has just did a dab in the House of Commons | Metro News
text:
Jimmy Nsubuga for Metro.co.uk Wednesday 22 Feb 2017 3:18 pm Labour party deputy leader Tom Watson does the ‘dab’ (Picture: PA) 
It’s taken a while but MPs are now dabbing in the House of Commons. 
That probably spells an end to the international dance craze because we doubt anyone else will want to do it now. 
Dab lovers can blame Labour’s deputy leader Tom Watson. 
The MP for West Bromwich East did the dance during Prime Minister’s Questions. 
Jeremy Corbyn had just finished asking Theresa May to invest in the NHS when his 50-year-old deputy decided to do the jig. But instead of looking like this He looked like this To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that supports HTML5 video 
He later confirmed what everyone had suspected. 
‘Did I do a dab? I’ve been doing them with my kids in the holidays so I may have inadvertently done one,’ he told Huffington Post’s Paul Waugh after leaving Prime Minister’s Questions. Some people loved his dance moves Tom Watson dabbing in PMQ has made my day, 😂😂 absolutely creased. #PMQs #Dab 
— Chris Ring (@RingySFC) February 22, 2017 As if Tom Watson did a dab in PMQs😂😂 #PMQs But others were not impressed As if Labour didn't look unprofessional enough already, Tom Watson decides to start dabbing at #PMQs . 🤦🏻‍♂️ 
— Adam Singh Hayer (@ASinghHayer) February 22, 2017 Really hope Tom Watson doesn't have to resign in some sort of PMQs dab betting scandal. 
— Conor Pope (@Conorpope) February 22, 2017 Evidence that Tom Watson dab was no accident. Well he could hardly smuggle a pie into the chamber… pic.twitter.com/fcGfQbvsr1 
— Alex Wickham (@WikiGuido) February 22, 2017 
And when a spokesman for the Prime Minister was asked if she knew what dabbing was, he replied: ‘I beg your pardon. Is it a radio?’ More
